I faced an incident at a store (Beauty SK Supply Snellville Ga) where, instead of addressing the issue, they tried to distract by prolonging the transaction  and accusing my daughter of theft when she walked by fake bracelets. As a jeweler, she’s focused on authentic pieces, not costume jewelry. It’s disheartening; perhaps it’s her skin or her natural hair, but assuming she steals and assuming she was a grown-up is absurd. Such assumptions based on appearances perpetuate unfair stereotypes.
